dataIdInfo.idAbs: This polygon shapefile represents zip code tabulation areas (ZCTAs) for the state of California. These data were gathered from the 2010 Census demographics update and contain keys for ZCTAs, centroid coordinates, demographic fields for age, gender, race and ethnicity, and housing information including living quarters, institutionalized populations, households and housing units. For the 2010 Census, there were no XX or HH ZCTAs assigned. Only five-digit ZCTAs were produced, and large unpopulated areas were excluded from the delineations. For the 2010 Census, there is no wall-to-wall national coverage for ZCTAs. Large water bodies and unpopulated land area such as national parks were excluded from the 2010 delineations, and for this reason the Census 2010 product does not have complete national coverage.

prcStep.stepDesc: The file tl_2010_06_zcta510 was downloaded from the US Census Bureau. It was projected to the Census2010 GDB. It was named tl_2010_06_zcta510_Projected. A new feature class, CensusZCTAs2010_Demographics, was created based on a schema developed by OSHPD and VESTRA. Records from tl_2010_06_zcta510 were appended to CensusZCTAs2010_Demographics with field mapping for key fields. Two Census data files, DEC_10_DP_DPDP1_with_ann.xlsx and DEC_10_SF1_QTP13_with_ann.xlsx, were manipulated into a file, CensusZCTA2010Data for compatibility with Esri technology and added to the Census2010 GDB. Table CensusZCTA2010Data was joined to feature class CensusZCTAs2010_Demographics and fields in the feature class related to population; age; gender; race; ethnicity; living quarters; institutionalized population; households; and housing units table were calculated based on the join.
